PURPOSE
  Shell script to manage a null zone file for BIND DNS server.

STATUS
  Working as of: 2014-08-17

DETAILS
  This script allows adding, removing, and displaying a sorted
  list of domain names to be used in a BIND null zone file.
  There is also support for adding comments alongside each
  entry. Requies awk, sed, and grep. Tested on Debian.

INSTALL
  01 : Modify the file paths in the script to suit where
       your null zone files are.
  02 : Optionally modify the output messages.
  03 : Copy nzedit to /usr/local/sbin and chmod +x.
  04 : Use and enjoy.

